    ("LOC_LOADING_INFO_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA",                                             "Prince Nyatsimba Mutota, around 1430, you travelled to the north of the region in search of salt. When the ancient Zimbabwe began its military and economic decline, some of the elite’s of the city migrated two hundred miles to the north to Zambezi River. As a result of their settlement, the Shona state of Monomotapa, commonly known Mutapa was established but it was short-lived. The ruler of this state was you, Mutota, and you were their first king. You gained control of the producing sites and a great portion of Zambezi Valley.[NewLine]Can you build now a civilization that will stand the test of time? "),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_TITLE",                                 "Nyatsimba Mutota"),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_SUBTITLE",                              "Mwene"),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_QUOTE",                                 "The old man gives the best advice."),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1",                "The only information we have about Nyatsimba Mutota comes from oral tradition. It is recorded that the warrior prince named Nyatsimba Mutota from the Kingdom of Zimbabwe was sent to find new sources of salt in the north. Prince Mutota found his salt among the Tavara, a Shona subdivision, who were prominent elephant hunters. They were conquered and a capital was established 350 km north of Great Zimbabwe at Zvongombe by the Zambezi. With Mutota as ruler, the Kingdom outgrew its parent state and became the dominant force in the region, mainting nominal independence from the powerful Portugese colonialist in Mozambique. Mutota's empire remained until, in the 17th century, rivalry between the Portugese and the Rozwi Empire (heralding from the Zimbabwe Plateau where Mutota was born) ripped it apart."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                                     "Welcome! I am Nyatsimba Mutota, the prodigal Prince. How did you hear about Zimbabwe?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_VISIT_RECIPIENT_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                     "It is a pleasure to meet you. Come and have a seat!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_NEAR_INITIATOR_POSITIVE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",             "So be it."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_FIRST_MEET_NO_MANS_INFO_EXCHANGE_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",               "Welcome among us, tell us more about your capital!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_GREETING_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                                       "Dumilani (Greetings)!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DELEGATION_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                   "We welcome your delegation with joy!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DELEGATION_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                   "Not today."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DELEGATION_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                             "Gifts of Kapentas and Sadza are brought to you by my delegation. We offer them to you. Have a nice diner!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                 "We have nothing to fear from your military. You may pass."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                 "You may not pass through our lands. It is closed to you."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_OPEN_BORDERS_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                           "Let us pass through your lands! We may be founding a new capital 300 kilometers north."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",               "Let's celebrate our friendship!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",               "No, sorry!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                         "Do you prefer vassalage or friendship?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                  "Thank you!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                  "Are you kidding?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_ALLIANCE_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                          "Would you like to form an alliance with us?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_KUDO_EXIT_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                                      "You are actually worthy of interest, what chance to meet you!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_WARNING_EXIT_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                                   "Your interest are conflicting with ours. Be careful."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_WARNING_TOO_MANY_TROOPS_NEAR_ME_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                "You cannot surprise the Great Mwene, you know?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_MAKE_DEAL_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                       "{LOC_DIPLO_ACCEPT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY}"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_MAKE_DEAL_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                       "{LOC_DIPLO_REJECT_DECLARE_FRIEND_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY}"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DENOUNCE_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                            "I will tell the truth to the other leaders: you worry us."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DENOUNCE_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                               "You are a sore! (Denounces You)."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_WAR_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                         "We can read on your mausoleum that you were daring, or rather that you had gone mad at the end..."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DECLARE_WAR_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                            "Well, we need land, and yours are there, waiting to be picked."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_AI_ACCEPT_DEAL_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                      "So let's make peace."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_AI_REFUSE_DEAL_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                      "I do not accept."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MAKE_PEACE_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                             "Can we stop this childishness and talk about business?"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DEFEAT_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                                 "Ophir has crumbled. The Zimbabwe birds have all left their roost. When you kill me, you will have destroyed all that remains of my people!"),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_DEFEAT_FROM_HUMAN_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY",                              "[LOC_DIPLO_DEFEAT_FROM_AI_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_ANY]"),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_LTRAIT_NAME",                                        "Rise of Mutapa"),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_LTRAIT_DESCRIPTION",                                 "Early Empire and Feudalism each grant an additional [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Route Capacity when researched. Get +1 [ICON_GreatMerchant] Great Merchant point from each level of Walls.[NEWLINE][ICON_Unit] Units that start their turn adjacent to a river gain +10 [ICON_Strength] Combat Strength."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GEDEMO_ZIMBABWE_CIV_TRAIT_NAME",                             "Journey beyond the Devasted Lands"),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_GEDEMO_ZIMBABWE_CIV_TRAIT_DESCRIPTION",                      "Internal [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes give +2 Loyalty to to their cities of origin.[NEWLINE]International [ICON_TradeRoute] Trade Routes grant additional +1 [ICON_Culture] Culture and +1 [ICON_Gold] Gold which are increased (+2) by the number of Camps or Plantations in the destination city."),
    ("LOC_UNIT_GEDEMO_ROZWI_NAME",                                                        "Uajero"),
    ("LOC_UNIT_GEDEMO_ROZWI_DESCRIPTION",                                                 "Zimbawe Civilization exclusive Unit that replaces the Spearman. Slightly stronger in combat, this unit has a similar cost. Available with Mining instead of Bronze Working."),
    ("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_UNIT_GEDEMO_ROZWI_NAME",                                     "Zimbabwe Unique Unit : Uajero"),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_UNITS_PAGE_UNIT_GEDEMO_ROZWI_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1",                     "The history of this country is also obscure. We only know that one of the elephant hunters (Uajero), who came from Changoe under the leadership of a resolute black man named Mutota (from the family of Ghangamira), and attracted by the staves and the salt that had spread in the country Mutonga de Ghemida, named Netondo (the creditor of the white people of Te te), began the conquest of this great territory, without being able to complete it at the same time, because death removed their chief, at the top of the Serra Chitacoxangonha, near of this promised land."),
    ("LOC_CIVILIZATION_GEDEMO_ZIMBABWE_DESCRIPTION_JFD_CIVILIZATION",                     "Zimbabwean Civilization"),
    ("LOC_AGENDA_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_NAME",                                                     "Mwenemutapa"),
    ("LOC_AGENDA_GEDEMO_MUTOTA_DESCRIPTION",                                              "Tries to build the widest network of alliances possible, and likes civilizations that do the same. Dislikes civilizations that don't establish networks."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MODIFIER_MATOPE_MANY_ALLIANCES",                                          "The Leader approves of your alliance-making."),
    ("LOC_DIPLO_MODIFIER_MATOPE_FEW_ALLIANCES",                                           "The Leader is unhappy you are in so few alliances."),
    ("LOC_ABILITY_MUTOTA_NAME",                                                           "Mutota's band"),
    ("LOC_ABILITY_MUTOTA_DESCRIPTION",                                                    "+10 Combat Strength starting on river."),
    ("LOC_IMPROVEMENT_GEDEMO_DZIMBABWE_NAME",                                             "Dzimbabwe"),
    ("LOC_IMPROVEMENT_GEDEMO_DZIMBABWE_DESCRIPTION",                                      "Masonry unlocks the Builder ability to construct Dzimbabwes, unique improvement to Great Zimbabwe. [NEWLINE]+2 [ICON_FOOD] Food. +2 [ICON_GOLD] Gold. +1 [ICON_HOUSING] Housing.[NEWLINE]Cities receive +1 [ICON_AMENITIES] Amenity from their first Dzimbabwe Improvement. Upon discovering Natural History, cities receive +1 [ICON_AMENITIES] Amenity from their second Dzimbabwe Improvement.[NEWLINE]Tiles receive +1 [ICON_GOLD] Gold if adjacent to a Dzimbabwe. +4 [ICON_Strength] Defense Strength for occupying units. Cannot be constructed adjacent to one another."),
    ("LOC_PEDIA_IMPROVEMENTS_PAGE_IMPROVEMENT_GEDEMO_DZIMBABWE_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1",   "A Dzimbabwe is a walled fort or citadel. It was a place for the local leader to live, and a point of defense in case of city attack. Dzimbabwe is a Shona name that, while the translation varies, can mean houses of stone. The ruins contain numerous stone enclosures with soaring walls as tall as 11 meters (36 feet). They were made without the use of mortar. Some scholars think that the city's rulers secluded themselves in a hilltop area where they could conduct rainmaking ceremonies, while others think that the city's rulers were willing to mix with people from different walks of life. Some scholars also think that the city's rulers didn't have a permanent palace but that when a ruler died the heir ruled from wherever they happened to be living at the time.");


