    ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_GREAT_PERSON_INDIVIDUAL_SUK_LAWSPEAKER_TEITUR_THORVALDSSON_NAME",                                                   "泰图尔·索瓦尔德松"),
    ("zh_Hans_CN",  "LOC_PEDIA_GREATPEOPLE_PAGE_GREAT_PERSON_INDIVIDUAL_SUK_LAWSPEAKER_TEITUR_THORVALDSSON_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1",          "【译者注：正在翻译……】[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Teitur Þorvaldsson was an Icelandic Lawspeaker in the 13th century. He was from the family of Haukdælar, son of Þorvaldur Gissurarson in Hruni and half-brother of Gissur Þorvaldsson. Teitur was ordained a priest and lived in Bræðratunga. He was a Lawspeaker from 1219 to 1221 and again from 1236 to 1247. He was said to be a wise and humble man who promoted reconciliation."),
